# GDS-VERO compliance — mandatory for UI work

When you **create or materially change React UI** (`.tsx` / `.jsx`):

1. **Follow** the **GDS-VERO compliance review** section in `GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md` (stack, imports, Chakra v3, semantic tokens, vero surfaces, typography, responsive layout, **component API verified against GDS docs**).
2. **Before writing compound components** (`Accordion`, `Dialog`, `Tabs`, `Menu`, `Field`, …): read the GDS docs page or `apps/docs/.../*Page.tsx` — do **not** guess slot names from memory.
3. **Complete the checklist** in that section before finishing. Fix violations in code when you can.
4. **Run lint** when available (`pnpm --filter docs lint` in monorepo; `npm run lint` / `pnpm lint` in scaffolded apps).
5. **End every UI delivery** with the full **Delivery audit report** from `GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md` §3 — all headings, all categories (**Design System**, **Chakra v3 API**, **Surface tokens**, **Typography**, **Accessibility**, **Responsive layout**), **Compliance Status** (PASS / WARNING / FAIL), **Deviations**, **Recommended follow-ups**, **Lint**. Do **not** skip or shorten.

Common fixes: import `Card` from `@chakra-ui/react` not `@gds-vero/react`; use `Card.Root variant="outline"` not `bg="bg.muted"`; use `GDSText textStyle="body"` not `textStyle="sm"`; page `bg="bg.subtle"`; Chakra compounds inherit 18px body from `@gds-vero/theme` ≥ 0.1.17 — do not add manual `fontSize="sm"` unless overriding; verified patterns in agent guide: **Accordion**, **Dialog** (not `Modal`), **Tabs** (not `TabList`), **Field** (not `FormControl`), **Card** (`Card.Title` not `GDSText` bold), **VeroMainHeader** (not custom header `Box`).

Canonical guide: `GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md` (monorepo root) or `node_modules/@gds-vero/react/GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md` (scaffolded apps).
